SIMPLE: partake
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Partake
<hw>Par*take"</hw> <pr>(p⟦aum⟧r*t⟦amac⟧k")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Partook</conjf>
<pr>(p⟦aum⟧r*t⟦oocr⟧k")</pr>; <pos>p. p.</pos> <conjf>Partaken</conjf>
<pr>(p⟦aum⟧r*t⟦amac⟧k"'n)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Partaking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[<ets>Part</ets> +
<ets>take</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To take a part, portion, lot, or share, in common
with others; to have a share or part; to participate; to share; <as>as,
to <ex>partake</ex> of a feast with others</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Brutes
<xex>partake</xex> in this faculty.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When I against myself with thee <qex>partake</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To have something of the properties, character, or
office; -- usually followed by <ptcl>of</ptcl>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The attorney of the Duchy of Lancaster <qex>partakes</qex> partly
of a judge, and partly of an attorney-general.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1046 --></p>

<p><ent>partake</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: partake
<hw>par*take"</hw> <pr>(p⟦aum⟧r*t⟦amac⟧k")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To partake of; to have a part or share in; to
share.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let every one <qex>partake</qex> the general joy.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To admit to a share; to cause to participate; to
give a part to.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spencer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To distribute; to communicate.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>partaker</ent>⟦br⟧
